ayman islands the company was cofounded by alan howard and four others in  it was once described as one of the largest macro hedge funds in the world with  billion in assets under management aum as of october before downsizing to  billion in   contents  history  investment funds history  corporate affairs  see also  references  external links historyedit brevan howard was cofounded in  by former credit suisse traders alan howard jeanphilippe blochet chris rokos james vernon and trifon natsis the company name was created by utilizing portions of the last names of the cofounders blochet took a sabbatical in  returned and left the firm again in november  vernon left his position as chief executive officer ceo in  but returned to the company as group chief operating officer coo in september  another cofounder rokos retired from the company in  the company received  billion to manage in the global macro fund from credit suisse private bank under the leadership of brevan howards founding partner assets grew to  billion in  the company generated a  return in  and returns from their global macro fund continued to perform well during the financial crisis of  in  the company moved its headquarters from london to geneva in july  the firm opened an affiliate firm in new york called brevan howard us investment management lp which had about  million in assets under management by  the company had established brevan howard capital management lp on the island of jersey as of june  it was reported to be the largest european hedge fund management firm based on its total aum an april  article in the financial news described the company as the biggest and bestperforming hedge fund management firm in europe in  the company reduced its workforce by about  due to reduced management assets and diminishing returns the fund had further losses in  and  and had only  billion in assets as of october  by  the firm had reduced its assets under management aum from  billion spread across nine funds 